'''''A Horse and Two Goats and Other Stories''''' (also published as ''A Horse and Two Goats'') is a collection of short stories by [[R. K. Narayan]], published in 1970 by [[The Bodley Head]].<ref>{{cite book|title=British book news|publisher=[[British Council]]|year=1970|pages=900|oclc=1537139}}</ref> The book is illustrated by [[R. K. Laxman]], Narayan's brother, and includes five stories.<ref>{{cite book|last=May|first=Charles Edward|others=Frank Northen Magill|title=Critical Survey of Short Fiction: Bharati Mukherjee - Mona Simpson|publisher=Salem Press|year=2001|edition=2|series=Critical survey of short fiction|volume=5|pages=1753|isbn=978-0-89356-011-9|oclc=248496155}}</ref> The title story is a sly narrative of a business transaction between an American tourist and an Indian goat-herder as the result of an inability to communicate with each other.<ref>{{cite book|last=Pritchett|first=Victor Sawdon |title=The Oxford book of short stories|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=1981|pages=395|isbn=978-0-19-214116-3|oclc=8035224}}</ref>
