'''Technological didactics''' is an English translation of ''Didáctica Tecnológica'', a common term in [[Spanish language|Spanish]] educational discourse.<ref>Francisco G. Paulino and Oliver Ramos A., [http://www.historiadominicana.com.do/component/content/article/241-qdidactica-tecnologica-para-la-ensenanza-de-la-historiaq.html ''Didáctica tecnológica para la enseñanza de la historia''], Historia Dominicana, 8 March 2009</ref><ref>Fer Garcia, [https://www.scribd.com/doc/215256599/104930941-Caracteristicas-de-La-Didactica-Tecnologica ''Características de la Didáctica Tecnológica''], Scribd.com, 30 March 2014</ref><ref>[http://www.slideshare.net/GRUPOPOSGRADO/comic-didactica-tecnologica ''Comic didactica tecnologica''], Slideshare, 29 May 2013</ref> It refers to the study of the influence of [[technology]] upon [[didactics]]. This field seeks to elucidate the role of technology within the various educational settings, and its direct and indirect influence upon the process of teaching and learning.

It starts with a specific analysis of each of the didactic components: objectives, content, method, medium, evaluation, and organizational forms; and finally a high-level analysis of the relationships among each of those components, always incorporating the technological component.

As a distinct body of knowledge relating to teaching methods, technological didactics developed during the 1990s, with the introduction of new technology into teaching. [[Linguistics|Linguistic]], [[Cultural studies|cultural]], and [[cognitive]] perspectives have all contributed.<ref>Litwin Edith, [http://cmapspublic.ihmc.us/rid=1GNWMM0B7-1L1N1LP-P7D/NT_Litwin.pdf ''Tecnologías educativas en tiempos de Internet'']. Amorrortu editores, Buenos Aires, 1st edition 2005. {{ISBN|950-518-833-1}}.</ref>

