'''Epanodos''' is a [[figure of speech]] used when the same [[word]] or two similar words are repeated within a passage of text.<ref name="Maunder1841">{{cite book|author=Samuel Maunder|title=The scientific and literary treasury|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mWw3sbiCWtAC&pg=PT246|accessdate=25 September 2013|year=1841|publisher=Longman|page=246}}</ref><ref name="Crabb1823">{{cite book|author=George Crabb|title=Universal Technological Dictionary Or Familiar Explanation of the Terms Used in All Arts and Sciences: Containing Definitions Drawn from the Original Writers : in Two Volumes|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jlZBAAAAcAAJ&pg=PT616|accessdate=25 September 2013|year=1823|publisher=Baldwin, Cradock & Joy|page=616}}</ref><ref name="Jacobs1969">{{cite book|author=Noah Jonathan Jacobs|title=Naming-day in Eden: The Creation and Recreation of Language|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ztu2AAAAIAAJ|accessdate=25 September 2013|year=1969|publisher=Macmillan|page=131}}</ref>

